Package: CaprForExtensions
Type: Package
Title: Extension Table Support for Capr Cohort Definitions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jared", "Houghtaling", email = "houghtaling@ohdsi.org", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Martijn", "Scheumie", email = "scheumie@ohdsi.org", role = c("aut"))
    )
Description: Extends the Capr package to support cohort definitions that reference
    OMOP CDM Extension Tables. Uses a placeholder substitution approach: extension
    criteria are converted to observation queries with special placeholder markers
    during compilation, CirceR generates standard SQL treating them as observations,
    then placeholders are substituted with actual extension table logic in post-processing.
    This enables leveraging all CirceR features (temporal logic, inclusion rules, attrition)
    while maintaining simple, robust implementation. Supports custom domains, temporal
    relationships, and multi-table joins.
